##<a id="1-5-0"></a> v1.5.0

**Release Date:** MMMM DD, YYYY

### Breaking Changes

This release has the following breaking changes:

- **subsume functionality for Azure SQL MSSQL Database Instance and Azure SQL MSSQL Failover Group has been removed:**
  From now on, it will not be possible to subsume an Azure SQL MSSQL Database Instance or an Azure SQL MSSQL Failover
  Group. The plan preconfigured in the brokerpak has also been eliminated.
  To learn more about the implications, please read the [upgrading documentation](upgrading.html.md.erb#procedure).

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

#### General

- **Terraform upgraded to v1.4.6:**
  The Terraform version used to apply changes is upgraded from v1.1.9 to v1.4.6.
  You must upgrade all service instances. When you upgrade, ensure that you follow the [Upgrade procedure](upgrading.html.md.erb#procedure).

### Resolved Issues

This release has the following fixes:

<%= partial vars.path_to_partials + '/csb/timeout-resolved' %>

- **Fixed error `Argument list too long` when starting the application:**
  When configuring the Cloud Service Broker with a long list of server pairs the application threw an error 
  `Argument list too long` due to reaching the maximum limit allowed by the operating system when setting 
  environment variables. From now on, the application set the necessary variables in a more efficient way.

